Note I did not see any current Burger King specials on the menu.   The 116th BK has the advertised specials out on display and you get quick not confusing service.  On  March 1st I came in around 12:30 pm and waited over 25 minutes for my order.  I understand this location just opened, however they are not organized.   I also was not the only customer having the issue. I had over 20 plus customers pass my order.   My food was actually ready but they held it without calling my number.  I had to push my way to the order pickup spot and try to flag a worker down.  The pickup space is very frustrating and cramped.  You can also hardly hear when they call your number out.  The music is blasting over the workers and a entrance doorway is also there bringing noise in.    I witnessed angry customers who ordered after me and their orders were incorrect. These customers were given wrong items or not all in their bags.    When I approached a worker about a customer who was waiting long before me for their order they brushed me off.  A month or 2 from now I will come here again and check on the service.
